<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41066a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41066a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41066a"> 66(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a Satan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Every man after death comes at first into the world of spirits, which is intermediate between heaven and hell, and there accomplishes his times or his states, and according to his life is prepared either for heaven or for hell. So long as he remains in that world he is called a spirit: he who is raised out of that world into heaven is called an angel; but he who is cast down into hell is called <mark>a satan</mark> or a devil. <small> Emanuel Swedenborg, <a name="ESAW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESAW"><cite title="source">Angelic Wisdom Concerning the Divine Love</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 140</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
